field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Trimi, John, Legend. Trimi is Pt, John is rutile Ru(18)O2, and Legend is rutile Ir(18)O2
field_data.Removed from vacuum: Legend quickly moved from Sputter chamber to Thetaprobe today, then

notes: Removed the chip that was present and put it in the sample box labeled "...Antimonate..." since I associate with it the contamination seen yesterday. Everything freshly aqua regia'd. 01... fucking tilt. No sign of electrolyte leakage. Where is the tilt coming from??? remounted. Sample had been protruding. Used Al foil and pressed the Pt hard against it. S 02... Still fucking tilt! Plus some extra peaks in CV, maybe due to Al??? I can't trust the RE_vs_RHE calibration with this fucking tilt, but don't have time to solve this bullshit. What the fuck is it?! There was no tilt yesterday, just contamination. Is that better to trust? The tilt might be worth as much as -50 uA at 0 V vs RHE. How much does that actually effect the OCP in H2 saturated electrolyte? I should be able to calculate the answer. The OCP in inert electrolyte is about 0.2-0.4 V vs RHE, which is near the intercept of the tilt, but also near where OCP normally would be, about +0.95 V vs RHE. I wonder if OCP is never effected by tilt? RE_vs_RHE = 0.660 Okay, I got 0.656 a number of times, 0.666 yesterday, 0.660 today. Can I just trust it iand move on? fuck this I want to Julebal. No sleeping in tomorrow. ------ 19L22 --------- the three John4 samples were dropped on the ground on 19L21. None landed face down, but all might be dirty. 03... John4A. First mount, air doesn't come down. I don't have extra of these samples, so gotta get it right. Remounted, electrolyte from first mount added to OCP electrolyte. Slow air response. 10 mV noise on OCP ;( . But going for it. I don't have all day. ... John4B Stub is too small to stay in the cell ;( I'm leaving this out with a drop of electrolyte on it for about 30 minutes as a type of control 04... John4C 30 uA. Shit, there's a slight chance I mixed up John4B and John4C. Damnit. Probably got them sorted out though. 05... Legend4A [previously Love4A] beautiful 100 uA. 06... Trimi1 Control OER, collected at 2 and 10 min. Left it cycling while I ate, but forgot to set repeats so instead got some repeat OER's. Then did cycles while setting up ISS. Looks like there's still a goddamn tilt... RE_vs_RHE has not moved since yesterday. I am confident on all the potentials measured today!!! RE_vs_RHE also does not move when I inject fresh electrolyte from the syringe (displacing electrolyte that had come from the bottle)... Since this is the last day doing experiments in 2019, and I just got my PhD diploma in the mail yesterday, I just want to say for the record of this elog: 2019 has been a turbulent year for this Dr. Scott. Let's make sure it was not in vain!
